#All samples are kept
detP<-detectionP(rgSet) # this gets the p-values
keep <- colMeans(detP) < 0.05
rgSet <- rgSet[,keep]

# remove poor quality samples from targets data
targets <- targets[keep,]
#targets[,1:5]
# remove poor quality samples from detection p-value table
detP <- detP[,keep]

# ensure probes are in the same order in the mSetSq and detP objects
detP <- detP[match(featureNames(GRset.funnorm),rownames(detP)),] 
# remove any probes that have failed in one or more samples
keep <- rowSums(detP < 0.01) == ncol(GRset.funnorm) 
table(keep)
## keep
##  FALSE   TRUE 
##  22164 463348
filter_rgSet <- GRset.funnorm[keep,]

keep <- !(featureNames(filter_rgSet) %in% ann450k$Name[ann450k$chr %in% 
                                                         c("chrX","chrY")])
table(keep)
## keep
##  FALSE   TRUE 
##  10370 452978
filter_rgSet <- filter_rgSet[keep,]


# remove probes with SNPs at CpG site
filter_rgSet <- dropLociWithSnps(filter_rgSet)

# exclude cross reactive probes 
library(maxprobes)
filter_rgSet <- maxprobes::dropXreactiveLoci(filter_rgSet)

Combat batch effect correction + SVA for surrogate variable. SVA applied to top 50k variable rows

pheno_data <- merge(pData(filter_rgSet),cellCounts,by=0)
myCombat<-champ.runCombat(beta=getBeta(filter_rgSet),pd=pheno_data,variablename="Sample_Group",batchname=c("Slide","Array"))
## ~Sample_Group + Array
## <environment: 0x3716d32a8>
## ~Sample_Group
## <environment: 0x3716d32a8>
library(sva) 
mod = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+PMI+NeuN_neg+NeuN_pos,data=pheno_data)
mod0 = mod[,-c(2)] 
n.sv<-num.sv(myCombat, mod, method = "be", vfilter = 50000, B = 20,seed = NULL)
n =n.sv
sva = svaseq(myCombat,mod,mod0, n.sv =n)$sv 
## Number of significant surrogate variables is:  14 
## Iteration (out of 5 ):1  2  3  4  5
colnames(sva)<-paste("sv", 1:n, sep = "")
pd_sva<-cbind(pheno_data,sva)


#Correct known and unknown confounders
design = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+PMI+NeuN_neg+NeuN_pos+sv1+sv2+sv3+sv4+sv6+sv7+sv8+sv9+sv10+sv11+sv12+sv13,data=pd_sva)
Y<-myCombat
X<-as.matrix(design)
beta = (solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%t(X))%*%t(Y)
myRegress= Y - t(X[,c(3:ncol(X))] %*% beta[c(3:nrow(beta)),])
